    label "0"
    text "Mental health is not just the absence of disorder&#8212;it&#8217;s a dynamic state of psychological, emotional, and social well-being"
  ]
  node [
    id 1
    label "1"
    text " What makes it particularly complex is that mental experiences are both biologically grounded and deeply contextual, shaped by personal history, cultural expectations, and social support structures"
  ]
  node [
    id 2
    label "2"
    text " Anxiety, depression, OCD, and trauma-related conditions are some of the most common struggles, but they rarely appear in pure forms"
  ]
  node [
    id 3
    label "3"
    text " Comorbidity is the rule, not the exception"
  ]
  node [
    id 4
    label "4"
    text " That&#8217;s why dimensional approaches to mental health are becoming more popular, replacing binary diagnostic labels with spectra"
  ]
  node [
    id 5
    label "5"
    text " One challenge is that mental illness is often invisible"
  ]
  node [
    id 6
    label "6"
    text " People may look fine while carrying tremendous internal distress"
  ]
  node [
    id 7
    label "7"
    text " And the stigma surrounding these conditions discourages many from seeking help"
  ]
  node [
    id 8
    label "8"
    text " Language plays a role here too&#8212;calling someone 'mentally ill' can reinforce the idea of brokenness rather than struggle or adaptation"
  ]
  node [
    id 9
    label "9"
    text " Effective treatment often requires a combination of interventions: medication to regulate neurotransmitters, therapy to reshape cognitive patterns, lifestyle changes to support mood regulation, and often, changes to the person&#8217;s environment"
  ]
  node [
    id 10
    label "10"
    text " No one-size-fits-all"
  ]
  node [
    id 11
    label "11"
    text " Trauma plays a bigger role in mental health than previously thought"
  ]
  node [
    id 12
    label "12"
    text " Experiences like abuse, neglect, or chronic stress during childhood leave marks not just emotionally but physiologically&#8212;altering stress response systems, memory consolidation, even brain development"
  ]
  node [
    id 13
    label "13"
    text " Preventive mental health care is just as important as treatment"
  ]
  node [
    id 14
    label "14"
    text " Building emotional literacy, resilience, and supportive social environments from a young age can buffer against a lot of suffering"
  ]
  node [
    id 15
    label "15"
    text " Yet in many places, mental health support only begins after crisis"
  ]
  node [
    id 16
    label "16"
    text " And we&#8217;re still learning"
  ]
  node [
    id 17
    label "17"
